### 🔐 **1. Try to Reset Your Password Using Microsoft 365 (Outlook)**
Most Outlook accounts are part of a Microsoft 365 (formerly Office 365) environment. You can reset your password using the official Microsoft login page.

**Steps:**
1. Go to [https://account.microsoft.com](https://account.microsoft.com)
2. Sign in with your Microsoft account (the one used for Outlook).
3. Click on **"Password"** under your profile.
4. Choose **"Change password"**.
5. Follow the prompts to create a new password.

> ✅ This works if you're using a personal Microsoft account (e.g., @outlook.com or @hotmail.com).

---

### 🏢 **2. If You’re Using a Work or School Account (Corporate Outlook)**
If your Outlook is tied to a company or school email (e.g., @company.com), the password reset process may be more restricted.

**What to do:**
- **Contact your IT department or system administrator.**  
